three reasons you’re getting in your own way 🫶🏼
•you’re not truly taking action, you’re waiting for something to happen. Even inaction is a choice.
•You believe you need a certain skill to succeed at your dreams and are forgetting that the dreams are possible because they come from within you.
•You’re waiting for the perfect time. Change is the only constant, there will never be a *perfect* time. There will likely be regret, however, for not starting sooner.

Water, vitamins, sunshine;
Extremes of anything can be dangerous.
When you’re looking at your food patterns, remember that if it won’t be sustainable long term it’s likely not for you. While it’s true that habits take time to build, restriction and diet tactics often lend way to short term physical changes but do nothing to help you connect with and understand your mental patterns. Start there, start small, and give yourself grace along the way ✨

I realized that one of my toxic patterns is delaying something until something else happens or stops 
“I’ll make more time for meal prep when I get caught up on rest”
“I’ll make plans for the weekends when they aren’t my only day off”
“I’ll invest in self care when I feel more financially well”
“I’ll FaceTime when I haven’t been on camera so much for meetings”
“I’ll work out more consistently when I’m not so tired from commuting”
“I’ll create more content when my screen time isn’t so high”
I could keep going. 
I regret delaying things, losing touch with things, thinking there’d be a day when suddenly there would be so much time. 
We have now. We are in the now. It’s not about being less busy, or life being less imbalanced. It’s about knowing what we want to make time for and doing the best we can with that gift of time AND being honest and kind when we don’t have any bandwidth to share. 💫
.
.
.
.

the thing with trauma…

those who know, check in when it happens.
those who find out, check in when you share about it.
and then it stops.
to no fault of their own, everyone else’s lives continue. 
they are not divided into “before” and “after”.
suddenly you feel needy, sensitive, challenged for doing things you need to do on your healing journey.
not even really beginning to be able to process until months or years later.
the check ins stop but the healing and recovery doesn’t. 
check in on your people. Even when the trauma is in the past and “stops” being the present. 
.
.
.
.

diet culture will always be around the corner of my brain ready to pull me back in
my digestion and energy have not been optimal so this morning my first thought was “I should order a juice cleanse to be delivered right now”
had it in my cart and everything.
never mind that juice cleanses have always exacerbated disordered thinking for me
never mind that I have always gotten a migraine during and after any juice cleanses that I’ve done.
the automatic “need” for this almost convinced me to do something I know doesn’t work for me.
rather than give into the impulsive thoughts, I ordered fresh produce, gut loving foods, and fresh juice and hydration. 
a juice cleanse for me lasts a day and leads to a distorted sense of well-being that then leads to migraines and then over-eating eating.
whole, real foods provide support and nourishment long past the empty bottles.
🫶🏼
.
.
.
.
